Description: Iterative simplification strategy for surface triangular grids augmented 
	with distributed data. Each iteration corresponds to an edge collapse where
	the selection of the edge to contract derives from a cost functional based 
	on both geometric and statistical-based considerations. 
	The library can	handle both zero and higher genus surfaces.
Reference: Dassi, F., Ettinger, B., Perotto, S., Sangalli, L.M. (2015),
	A mesh simplification strategy for a spatial regression analysis over the 
	cortical surface of the brain, Applied Numerical Mathematics, Vol. 90, pp. 111-131.	
	
